			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong><em>SAP Acquires SmartOps to Help Customers Optimize Inventory and Service Levels in Supply Chain</em></strong></p>
<p>
Position Title: Senior Software Developer &ndash; SmartOps Supply Chain Optimization</p>
<p>
<strong>Purposes and Objectives</strong></p>
<p>
SAP is looking for an experienced Software Developer to join our development team in the construction of HANA based supply chain optimization applications.&nbsp; We empower customers to run their businesses in real time &mdash; to analyze, predict, react and adjust instantly.</p>
<p>
The team is looking for a Software Developer who has excellent design and programming skills across multiple programming languages and technologies, including C++, Java, SQL, Java Script and REST Services. We work in an Agile/Scrum development environment.</p>
<p>
Bring your exceptional problem solving and software programming skills with the ability to learn new tools, systems and processes for cutting edge technologies in Supply Chain Management (SCM) and multi-stage inventory optimization solutions for SAP&rsquo;s enterprise customers globally.</p>
<p>
<strong>This position is located at SAP Lab&rsquo;s Pittsburgh, PA site</strong>.</p>
<p>
Link: http://www.smartops.com</p>
<p>
<strong>Expectations and Tasks</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Design, development and support of new and existing products in the SAP Supply Chain Optimization Product Suite<br />
&bull; Coordinate design and development of new features with other members of the team<br />
&bull; Participate on architecture and design discussions with other senior engineers and architects<br />
&bull; Review and provide constructive feedback on software requirements, design, architecture and test case documentation to other members of the Product Management, Engineering and QA teams<br />
&bull; Review and provide constructive feedback to code developed by other members of the Engineering team</p>
<p>
<strong>Education and Qualifications / Skills and Competencies</strong><br />
&bull; B.S. or M.S. in Computer Science or other Engineering field<br />
&bull; Must be able to interpret software requirements and translate them into software design documentation and ultimately into working code<br />
&bull; Must be able to participate on software requirements discussions with Product Owners and other senior engineers<br />
&bull; Must be able to participate on architecture discussions with other senior engineers and architects<br />
&bull; Object Oriented Programming in Java (Spring Framework) and C++<br />
&bull; Programming Framework experience (MVC &amp; MVP)<br />
&bull; HTML5, JavaScript (Dojo, jQuery), SAP UI5, CSS, REST Services<br />
&bull; Object-relational Mapping Frameworks<br />
&bull; Databases: Sybase ASE, MySQL, Oracle, SAP HANA<br />
&bull; Web Application Servers</p>
<p>
<strong>Work Experience</strong><br />
&bull; Minimum 5 years&rsquo; experience working with C++ or Java Enterprise Web Applications</p>
